_How is this different from the past 75% test?_ Adobe bidding is new and has very little historical data to inform bids (2 mo, since May 7 transition). Opening the cap will accelerate learning and it’s ability to broaden bid testing (ie. more throughput at 75% vs 65%). Early performance supports this assumption as expanding EU thresholds in wk 27 kept CVR and CPC static WoW while the increased traffic drove 11% more NB registrations. We are also maximizing traffic to our AVT campaigns which have higher activation rates (and thus CCP) vs general ads. As of today, we believe we’ve also found a path to broaden AVT targeting for increased volume. Lastly, we expect increased CCP with the introduction of Guest for Pending Verification users (65% PV engagement, rolled out Jun), Guest ability to support unregistered AB shopping (Q4), increased Personalization WW (personalized reg start, and on-MCS customer recognition for personalization of SMS/CPS value props [ETA mid Aug]). Largely this exercise serves as a mitigation technique until Google bidding is reestablished. We have found a path for resolution, however, timing is currently Q4 for US only.
 
