1. Campaign Restructure: Aligned with Modern Search Best Practices, the team has begun consolidating campaigns toward a streamlined structure. There are 2,600 campaigns in US which overlap due to superfluous and legacy segmentation (breakouts by device, attempts at customer size, match type, etc causing 36% kw repetition), which can inhibit intelligent bidding due to insufficient data per keyword instance. Current campaign restructure have already reduced ref tags by 22k. ETA EOQ1
2. Manual Bid improvement based on CCP: We are phasing Deep Dive of poor performing keywords individually to assess removal and bid improvements. Currently in Phase 1 (completion expected EO Jan), we are assessing 0-reg keywords with an est savings of $412k. For Phase 2, we will expand to low reg/high cost  terms, with continually scaling volume (ie. <5 reg by EO Feb, <20  reg, etc). 
    1. As Paid Search registrants have completed 6 pages of registration forms, we are confident lead quality is high and NonBrand CCP can be improved from $68 (US, Y23) with ongoing support from post-reg teams [Activation, Engagement].
